======================================================================
ANALYSIS 14: SKIP-ONE CLOSURE PROPERTY
======================================================================

Face regularity requires THREE conditions when deleting interior vertex v_i:
  1. v_{i-1} → v_{i+1} (new edge in face)
  2. v_{i-2} → v_{i+1} (new skip-one, if i≥2)
  3. v_{i-1} → v_{i+2} (new skip-one, if i≤m-2)

Condition 1 (edge): v_{i-1} beats v_{i+1}
Condition 2 (left skip): v_{i-2} beats v_{i+1}
Condition 3 (right skip): v_{i-1} beats v_{i+2}

For d²=0, we need: whenever conditions 1,2,3 create a 'missing' face,
the missing contributions must cancel in the alternating sum.
This is an algebraic cancellation, NOT just a combinatorial property.

